dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/21\/salat-responds-performance\/","url_meta":{"origin":38531,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Salat: The prayer responds to good or poor performance","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 21, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubadah ibn al-Samit reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen a man prays, performs ablution well, and perfects its bowing and prostration, the prayer says: May Allah preserve you as you have preserved me! When he performs his bowing poorly, neither perfecting its bowing\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33353,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/09\/05\/abdullah-weeping-pretend-cry\/","url_meta":{"origin":38531,"position":1},"title":"Abdullah on Weeping: Cry from fear of Allah, or pretend to cry","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Mulaykah reported: I was sitting with Abdullah ibn Amr, may Allah be pleased with him, by the stone of the Ka\u2019bah and he mentioned a prophetic tradition, then he said, \u201cWeep! If you do not find yourself weeping, then feign weeping. By the one in whose hand is\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":18569,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/03\/18\/saeed-prayer-different-sunnah\/","url_meta":{"origin":38531,"position":2},"title":"Sa\u2019id on Sunnah: Punished for praying differently from Sunnah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 18, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019id ibn al-Musayyib reported: He saw a man praying after sunrise at dawn with more than two cycles, and he was excessive in his bowing and prostration, so Sa'id prohibited him. The man said, \u201cO Abu Muhammad, will Allah punish us for praying?\u201d Sa\u2019id said, \u201cNo, but he will punish\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17071,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/12\/01\/sujud-sajdah-darajah\/","url_meta":{"origin":38531,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Sujud: Each prostration rewarded by a degree","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Dharr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo servant prostrates for the sake of Allah but that Allah will raise his status by a degree and expiate one of his sins.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 388 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0630\u0631 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5824,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/02\/virtue-masjid-al-haram-nabawi\/","url_meta":{"origin":38531,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Mosques: Virtue of praying at two sacred mosques","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 2, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah